===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|bere|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|beor|bēor|beer|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|biuzán||biuzáz|beer|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|beus-||bheus-|dross, sediment, brewer's yeast|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|fry|-}} {{term|bier||beer|lang=fry}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|beer||beer|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|bier||beer|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Bier||beer|lang=de}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|bjór||beer|lang=is}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|buska||freshly brewed beer, new beer|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|dum|-}} & {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|busen|būsen|lang=gml|lang=dum|to feast, booze, drink heavily}}, {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|bus|būs|lang=gmh|a swelling}}. More at {{l|en|booze}}.

